. do 04-exploring-categories-with-explore.do 

. *****************************************************************************
> ***
. * 04-exploring-categories-with-explore.do
. *
. * Use `catllm explore` for SATURATION ANALYSIS. Unlike `catllm extract`
. * (which de-duplicates and merges similar labels), `catllm explore`
. * returns every raw category string from every chunk across every
. * iteration -- with duplicates intact. That makes it the right tool for
. * understanding category stability: do the same themes keep appearing,
. * or are new ones still being discovered with each iteration?
. *
. * Use case: you have ~500 open-ended survey responses and want to know,
. * "If I sample 50 of them, am I capturing most of the themes? Or do I
. * need to look at all 500?"
. *
. * Requires: OPENAI_API_KEY (or set provider() to your preferred backend)
. * Cost:     ~$0.05 across the two runs below
. * Runtime:  ~30 seconds for the basic run + ~30 seconds for the iteration
. *           sweep
. *****************************************************************************
> ***
. 
. clear all

. set more off

. 
. adopath + "`c(pwd)'/.."
  [1]  (BASE)      "/Applications/StataNow/ado/base/"
  [2]  (SITE)      "/Applications/StataNow/ado/site/"
  [3]              "."
  [4]  (PERSONAL)  "/Users/chrissoria/Documents/Stata/ado/personal/"
  [5]  (PLUS)      "/Users/chrissoria/Library/Application Support/Stata/ado/plu
> s/"
  [6]  (OLDPLACE)  "~/ado/"
  [7]              "/Users/chrissoria/Documents/Research/cat-llm/stata-package/
> examples/.."

. 
. global OPENAI_API_KEY : env OPENAI_API_KEY

. if "$OPENAI_API_KEY" == "" {
.     di as error "OPENAI_API_KEY not set."
.     exit 198
. }

. 
. * --- Example data: reasons people gave for moving --------------------------
> --
. input str200 open_response

                                                                               
>                                                                              
>                                     open_response
  1. "The weather was just too hot where I lived"
  2. "I could no longer afford the rent in my old neighborhood"
  3. "My company offered me a promotion but it required relocating"
  4. "I wanted to be closer to my aging parents"
  5. "The schools in my old district were underperforming"
  6. "I needed a fresh start after my divorce"
  7. "The cost of living was eating up most of my paycheck"
  8. "I got accepted to a great university here"
  9. "My spouse got a new job in this city"
 10. "The crime rate where I lived was getting worse"
 11. "I wanted access to better healthcare"
 12. "The job market in my field was much better here"
 13. "I retired and wanted somewhere quieter"
 14. "My family kept asking me to move back home"
 15. "The political climate in my old state didn't fit me"
 16. "I wanted to be closer to nature and the outdoors"
 17. "My apartment building was sold and I had to leave"
 18. "I followed my partner who is doing a residency here"
 19. "The public transportation here is much better"
 20. "I always wanted to live in a city this size"
 21. end

. 
. * --- 1. Basic explore run with survey-question framing ---------------------
> --
. * domain(survey) routes through cat-survey which injects the survey question
. * into the prompt for more accurate theme discovery.
. di _n "{hline 60}"

------------------------------------------------------------

. di "1. Raw category extraction (12 iterations, 8 divisions)"
1. Raw category extraction (12 iterations, 8 divisions)

. di "{hline 60}"
------------------------------------------------------------

. 
. catllm explore open_response,                       ///
>     apikey($OPENAI_API_KEY)                         ///
>     model("gpt-4o-mini")                            ///
>     iterations(12)                                  ///
>     divisions(8)                                    ///
>     catsperchunk(10)                                ///
>     maxcategories(15)                               ///
>     description("Reasons people gave for moving to a new city")  ///
>     pyoptions("survey_question='Why did you move to this city?'")
Exploring categories from 20 observations...
(raw extraction, no deduplication -- for saturation analysis)
catstack.explore() failed: explore() got an unexpected keyword argument 'survey
> _question'
r(198);

end of do-file
r(198);
